{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"metadata": {"doc_id": "ceb9871ff7f3e6a8d096541175d13a17", "source": "NexaCorp Policy Handbook v5.2", "part": "4. Anti-Harassment, Discrimination & Equal Opportunity", "section": "4.3 Reporting & Investigation Procedures", "subsection": "4.3.1 Reporting Options", "raw_content": "Any employee who experiences or witnesses conduct they believe violates this policy is encouraged \u2014 and in some cases required under applicable mandatory reporting obligations \u2014 to report it promptly. Reports may be made to any of the following: The employee's direct manager (unless the manager is the subject of the complaint). Any member of the HR team, including the employee's assigned HR Business Partner. The Ethics Hotline (anonymous, 24/7): +1-800-NEX-ETIX or ethics.nexacorp.com. The Chief People Officer directly for complaints involving senior leaders. External reporting to the EEOC, state fair employment agencies, or equivalent international bodies.", "type": "text"}, "page_content": "Part: 4. Anti-Harassment, Discrimination & Equal Opportunity\n            Section: 4.3 Reporting & Investigation Procedures\n            Subsection: 4.3.1 Reporting Options\n            Any employee who experiences or witnesses conduct they believe violates this policy is encouraged \u2014 and in some cases required under applicable mandatory reporting obligations \u2014 to report it promptly. Reports may be made to any of the following: The employee's direct manager (unless the manager is the subject of the complaint). Any member of the HR team, including the employee's assigned HR Business Partner. The Ethics Hotline (anonymous, 24/7): +1-800-NEX-ETIX or ethics.nexacorp.com. The Chief People Officer directly for complaints involving senior leaders. External reporting to the EEOC, state fair employment agencies, or equivalent international bodies.", "type": "Document"}}